In my opinion,

ops.insert: Stress is detrimental to your physical and mental health and can take a toll on other areas of your life, so rather than letting stress "kill" you, I believe everyone should be proactive in learning healthy coping mechanisms through meditation and mindfulness.

Teaching mindfulness at a school is especially beneficial to it's students since school can be one of the most stressful and anxiety-inducing thing in one's life. Students can learn how to tackle negative emotions that sometimes come with school and those skills can translate into other areas of their life.
